<p>The <i>perlcgi</i> framework can be used to run <i>any</i> CGI script, but, like the <xref
        href="1.2index.dita#topic8895">perl</xref> framework, it provides ActivePerl in the default
  PATH and supports module installation via <xref href="1.2index.dita#topic8895/cpan-modules-via-ppm">PPM</xref> and <xref
        href="index.dita">
        <i>cpanm</i>
      </xref>.</p>
  <p>Unlike the perl framework, setting the <xref type="section" href="../../../deploy/1.2manifestyml.dita#topic20922/start-file" >
<i>start-file</i>
</xref> option
has no effect, as there is no permanently running application. A new
instance of a CGI script is started for each request.</p>
<p>Perl scripts deployed with this framework should begin with:</p>
<codeblock>#!/usr/bin/env perl</codeblock>
